This paper proposes a method for accelerating deep neural networks through filter pruning. The focus is on computer vision tasks, which suggests cs.CV as the most likely sub-category. The method involves adding an extra loss term to force filters in each cluster to be similar, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning and deep learning, indicating cs.LG and cs.AI as likely sub-categories. The paper also involves fine-tuning the pruned network, which is a common technique in neural network optimization, suggesting cs.NE as a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves experiments on benchmark datasets, which is a common practice in natural language processing and computer vision, indicating cs.CL as a possible sub-category.
